Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 787
S.P. 347 In Senate, March 4, 2025
to the Maine School of Science and Mathematics
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on February 27, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Education and Cultural Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator GROHOSKI of Hancock.
Cosponsored by Representative BABIN of Fort Fairfield and
Senators: LIBBY of Cumberland, RAFFERTY of York, Representatives: CARLOW of
Buxton, DODGE of Belfast, FROST of Belgrade, GERE of Kennebunkport, MURPHY of
Scarborough, SARGENT of York.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §8202, sub-§2, ¶A, as amended by PL 1995, c. 665, Pt. FF,
3 §1, is further amended to read:
4 A. The amount must be paid in 4 equal quarterly payments during the year of
5 attendance. The first payment must be made by July 31st. The amount of tuition and
6 other costs paid for all students is limited to the amount appropriated for this purpose.
7 To be eligible for state funding under this paragraph, a student must have resided reside
8 in Maine with a parent, other relative or guardian for at least 6 months immediately
9 preceding application to the school at the start of the academic year for which state
10 funding is appropriated.
11 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
12 allocations are made.
13 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
14 General Purpose Aid for Local Schools 0308
15 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds to the Maine School of Science and Mathematics to
16 support administrative operations.
17 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
18 All Other $400,000 $400,000
19 __________ __________
20 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $400,000 $400,000
2117 General Purpose Aid for Local Schools 0308
22 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds to the Maine School of Science and Mathematics to
23 allow the administration to give financial support to in-state students who demonstrate a
24 financial need related to paying room and board expenses.
25 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
26 All Other $250,000 $250,000
27 __________ __________
28 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $250,000 $250,000
2295
30 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
31 DEPARTMENT TOTALS 2025-26 2026-27
32
33 GENERAL FUND $650,000 $650,000
34 __________ __________
35 DEPARTMENT TOTAL - ALL FUNDS $650,000 $650,000
36
30 SUMMARY
3371 Current law requires that state funding for a student who applies to the Maine School
3382 of Science and Mathematics is available only if the student resided in Maine for at least 6
3393 months prior to applying to the school. This bill instead requires that the student reside in
4304 Maine at the start of the academic year for which state funds are appropriated. This bill
4315 also provides ongoing funds to the Maine School of Science and Mathematics to support
Page 1 - 132LR1822(01)
316 administrative operations and allow the administration to give financial support to in-state
327 students who demonstrate a financial need related to paying room and board expenses.
Page 2 - 132LR1822(01)
