30 SUMMARY
3371 Current law requires that state funding for a student who applies to the Maine School
3382 of Science and Mathematics is available only if the student resided in Maine for at least 6
3393 months prior to applying to the school. This bill instead requires that the student reside in
4304 Maine at the start of the academic year for which state funds are appropriated. This bill
4315 also provides ongoing funds to the Maine School of Science and Mathematics to support
Page 1 - 132LR1822(01)

316 administrative operations and allow the administration to give financial support to in-state
327 students who demonstrate a financial need related to paying room and board expenses.
